0ServicePot
03/07/12
Written by Midhat ALI (Unicam)

== WHAT IS IT? ==
ServicePot is a UDDI Registry for Web Service Choreographies. It provides functions to publish and retrieve Choreographies, in addition to the standard UDDI APIs for Web Services

== REQUIREMETNS ==

Before you compile the project you need to install

#1 Java 1.6 or later

#2 Apache Maven

== CONFIGURING IT ==

ServicePot uses a configuration file located at ServicePot/src/main/resources/UDDIProxy.properties
This file needs to contain URIs to endpoints of a standard UDDI Registry

== COMPILING IT ==

Compile the project by entering the command "mvn install" at the command prompt. This will generate the war file in the servicepot-war/target directory

== RUNNING IT ==

Deploy the war file from dist directory to a tomcat server installation

== VERIFYING IF IT WORKS ==

ApplicationURL = tomcat_server_address/name_of_the_war

Service Listing should be available at <ApplicationURL>/servicepot/services
A graphical OSGi console will be available at <ApplicationURL>/servicepot/servlet/console.
